cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a mathematical theory for data clustering based on a multivariate mutual information measure. This measure is related to information theory, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses applications of the theory to the human genome and connectome, which are related to machine learning and data analysis, falling under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper proposes new computationally feasible solutions, which are related to computational neuroscience and artificial intelligence, falling under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
